    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A thermoplastic adhesive that is already present in a thin layer on the adherend which, by the application of heat and pressure, forms the bond. Distinguished from "hot-melt adhesive" which necessitates application of the adhesive in the molten state.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Adhesivo termoplástico que se encuentra previamente presente como capa delgada sobre el adherente el cual, por aplicación de calor y presión, forma la unión. Se distingue del "adhesivo termofusionable", que necesita aplicación del adhesivo en estado fundido.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een thermoplastisch hechtmiddel dat al in een dunne laag op het te plakken oppervlak aanwezig is waar het, door aanwending van warmte en druk, de binding vormt. Te onderscheiden van 'smeltlijm' waarbij het hechtmiddel moet worden aangebracht in gesmolten toestand.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種熱塑性的膠黏劑，已塗有薄層在待膠接物上，可運用熱及壓力產生黏接。與「熱熔膠黏劑」並不相同，後者需要運用熔解狀態的膠黏劑來黏接。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
